
[1]discerning

   DISCERNING, ppr.

   1. Distinguishing; seeing; discovering; knowing; judging.

   2. a. Having power to discern; capable of seeing, discriminating,
   knowing and judging; sharp-sighted; penetrating; acute; as a discerning
   man or mind.

             DISCERNING, n. The act of discerning; discernment.
